🗄️ Data Modeling — Design This Before Writing a Query
Users
  └── uid, email, displayName, createdAt

Subjects
  └── id, userId, name, colorHex

Tasks
  └── id, userId, subjectId, title, description
      dueDate, priority (1-3), status (todo|inprogress|done)
      reminderAt, createdAt, updatedAt

Notifications
  └── id, userId, taskId, scheduledAt, sent (bool)
Key decisions:

Keep subjectId on every task — filtering by subject is the #1 query students will run
Store reminderAt as a separate field, not derived from dueDate — students want custom reminder windows
Never store notification state in the task document — separate collection = easier cleanup


